ieve they deserve every copy of the Holy Canon of the Gods, the Testament of Vanear.  They have forgotten that it is a holy text to all of us, not merely to the faithful of the Rainkeeper.&quot;<br><br>&quot;I am fearful that a rot may have set in in the heart of the great oak that are our brothers in Rivervale, and they must be once again taught that all things must be restored to the proper balance.&quot;<br><br>&quot;They, of all people, should know that if the rains collect only in one place, the rest of the continent parches, and that the region in which the rain collects festers.  In order for there to be growth, the rain must come to all places.&quot;<br><br>&quot;To this end, I urge all persons to act against their hoarding of the Holy Canon for themselves, and I call upon the faithful of the Rainkeeper to recognize that their actions are out of balance.&quot;<br><br>&lt;ooc&gt;<br><br>I think, at this point, it is difficult to doubt that the Order of the Oaken is farming the Testament of Vanear.  They may justify their actions because of the Trivial Loot Code, but the effect is the same: they're denying access to this item to other people who wish to acquire it fairly so that they may get as many copies as they need.  This needs to stop.<br><br>To that end, I urge people to engage in an old-fashioned 1960s &quot;sit-in&quot; at Dyllin's spawn site tomorrow, Saturday, December 22nd.  Come, sit an hour or two, and chat with others.<br><br>Rules for this sit-in:<br><br>1) Be polite to everyone there.  Do not be rude to anyone, including those who've been farming this item.<br>2) Because they've been 'farming' the Testament of Vanear and denying its access to anyone else, any rights the Order of the Oaken might claim to this camp should justifiably be ignored by any person or persons who could use this item for themselves and could acquire it for themselves.  Members of the Order of the Oaken get to go to the end of the line to wait for this item.<br>3) If Dyllin does show up during the course of the sit-in, and there are multiple people who could use Page 30 who don't already have Testaments of their own, work out equitably and fairly who it should go to ahead of time.<br>4) Don't kill-steal from anyone, including those who've been farming this item for the past couple days.<br><br>I'll be there for an hour or so.  If you agree that farming this item to the exclusion of others is outrageous, please join me in Highpass Hold tomorrow.<br><br>&lt;/ooc&gt;<br><br>Lasgalen, Sixteenth Autumn Initiate of Tunare<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A> at: 12/21/01 11:48:41 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalninil>Dalninil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/21/01 3:05:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=185.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Highpass Hold Sit-In: 12-22-01</span><hr size=1> KS by lag ! <br>make sure  to bring lots of AE spells<br>and we need bards.<br><br>next stop Hadden !<br>we will sit and watch folks wait hours and hours to get an item because it's fun.....<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uquillionthegnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quillion the Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/21/01 4:39:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=185.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top