ing to do with my role as a moderator.<br><br>Kimmz, I had no idea about this issue until I read this thread, and no preconceived opinions about either The Order of the Oaken (aside from it having a reasonably interesting name) or anyone else involved.  Your post alone immediately convinced me that your guild was proably in the wrong here.  Perhaps you should consider what that means?  Just a friendly suggestion.<br><br>Valquiss Silverpalm <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rumble>Rumble</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/26/01 3:21:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=185.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Highpass Hold Sit-In: 12-22-01</span><hr size=1> If any know me by reputation here or in game, know also that I am a member of the Order of the Oaken.  Do I have the same reputation as the few that this poster/sit-in organizer has had problems with? I surely hope not, and I cannot believe that many on this wonderful server would shun all Oaken because of the words of one person who had a bad experience with a few.  <br><br>I have seen this type of action on other servers, on both sides, and hoped not to find it here.  TLC makes some people do interesting things.  Dyllan has ALWAYS been a camp that gets people's dander up. Is it right to poison the name of an entire guild over the actions of a few? This was NOT a guildwide sanctioned action-- <br><br>Most all of my brethren in the Oaken are the most honorable, decent people on any server, which is why I continue to be a member and enjoy this unique server. My understanding is that this mess was worked out, yet the slams against an entire guild continue. 